⁣"It is easy to see the strategy of humans:
Build things that mimic nature in order to 'conquer' nature

Our species continues to try to impose its will using allows and electricity
But the rest of creation undermines us through water, wind, and fire

The reason that the cosmic joke works is its punchline:
We are as ephemeral as smoke from a newly extinguished candle.

And time marches on..."

This month's installment from Matthew Evan Taylor's #PostcardsToTheMet brings in the sounds of Ayane Kozasa on viola and Paul Wiancko on cello. 

Tune in each month to this #MetLiveArts project from composer and solo saxophonist Matthew Evan Taylor, in collaboration with Metropolis Ensemble and RAJAS, and get a glimpse into Taylor's creative process to exchange musical concepts globally for his evening-length piece "Life Returns," which will be presented at The Met in spring 2022.⁣⁣
